Big brother Naija has announced applications for it’s seventh edition. The reality TV show houses over 20 contestants to battle for a grand prize of N85million. Contestants must survive every eviction week and obey all big brother house rules for 71 days to emerge winner. The announcement reads: “Biggie is calling you back home #BBNaija Season 7 auditions are officially open, are you the next Efe, Miracle, Mercy, Laycon or Whitemoney? This is your time to show Biggie what you’re all about audition here: africamagic.tv/bbaudition Audition now!” The show started in 2006 with Katung Aduwak emerging winner.   Celebrities that split after engagement     Social media trends: Celebration galore for Ini Edo, Oga…     Lagos agog as reggae artistes excite fans to honour late Bob…   There was 11- year break before it auditioned for another season. Big brothers has churned out contestants who went on to become celebrities Winners for subsequent seasons were: Efe, Miracle, Mercy, Laycon and White money respectively. With every edition comes with a theme. The first season’s theme was “BBN”, Second and the third season was “See Gobe“ and Double Wahala”, fourth season; “Pepper Dem’, the fifth season was ‘Lockdown Edition’, and the sixth season was “Shine Ya Eyes” The theme for this year’s season is yet to be unveiled.